snippet.textDisplay:
I actually have friends that’s went through this very thing. The husband’s mom convinced him to break off his engagement to his wife a few days before the wedding, because the mom wanted him to be with his ex-girl who she loved dearly and wanted to be her daughter-in-law. Like a Dummy he did it (it was mainly because he actually still had feels for his ex, tried to move on, but once his mom tried to get them back together he said why not...even though he was in a year+ long relationship with his soon to be wife). The wife was heartbroken, but knew that the mom secretly didn’t like her, so she fought for her man despite being embarrassed lol. I told her she was crazy and was way better than me because I would’ve moved on. But once the wife was able to open his eyes to what his mom was really doing (and he also realized that his ex wasn’t worth 2 pennies) we went back to his wife and they immediately got married.

They have been happily married for 7 years and now have kids. The wife for sure is the driving force in the relationship and he will do any for her and he also started putting his foot down when it comes to his mom and how she was treating his wife (it took a while to get to the point). Besides that weird situation, I personally really admire their relationship.

snippet.textDisplay: First, he may or may not be lying about his mother saying he should break up with her, if he is, he probably doesnt want to say HIS personal reason for breaking up because he's trying not to hurt her feelings.  Two, regardless of why, the fact is he made the decision to go through with it. Therefore i think it will be hard to get over. In response to Loni, I do not think she should date right now period. No singular or multi dating. Not even with him. If he chooses to get back together I would suggest she say she needs time. See if he's interested within 3 or so months. Then you can know if it's worth giving it another shot after what he did. If people did that they could save themselves and others a lot of pain.

snippet.textDisplay: Listen,  I wanted to go through the screen to tell her to run. I lived what she is trying to do to herself and SURVIVED!! Nothing my ex-husband's mom did affected me but his reaction to it was so hurtful. He would not acknowledge or address what ever she did and whenever I mentioned it he would just not speak to me for days. At one point I was a stay at home mom because it was more economical to stay at home with our special needs child. Well, I was told, in public, that it was because of her son I could eat. Was told by her son that I was an anchor on his feet. Finally, he started cheated with a married woman who was comfortable enough to send gifts to our home. I have a degree, and not knocking anyone's hustle, and I became a night janitor at the airport so that we could be available for his corporate job and I stay at home with the children. After finding the gifts and videos of him taking to his girl, I searched his phone and found a message with his mom telling him to divorce me. He did, and initially I was thinking that I just started working and I have these two children. Well, God is always just! I bought my home less than one year after the divorce, I have a wonderful job in finance because I can finally get him to assist (court ordered) with his kids and it is not expected to be my job only. I look back now and think, all this time they said I was holding him back, he is still living in his apartment  and actually SEVERELY worst off than he was when we were married. I hope that girl knows that sometimes you have to protect your heart by leading with your brain. No man should disrespect their mom but he should be able to respectfully check his mom. Also, at 26 years old, we cannot blame his mother 100%, he is choosing to follow her directives. You may not have done anything wrong. Some mothers will never like a strong woman for their son. They wants someone who their son can walk all over! I think you are beautiful, what is ahead is far better than what you left behind. Press along, you will look back one day and praise God. Trust me!
